## Soon

- [x] Web bundle size — split mapbox-gl into separate chunk (MapPage: 1,685KB → 20KB)
- [ ] Add tile-proxy observability (cache hit ratio, upstream error rate, per-provider request volume)
- [ ] Versioned tile URLs for cache invalidation (before launch) — tile URLs (`/api/v1/tiles/{provider}/{z}/{x}/{y}`) have no version, so a content/source change can't be invalidated in the browser or CDN caches (only Redis, via manual flush — a dev-only hack). Add a per-provider cache version: include it in the URL (`/api/v1/tiles/v2/{provider}/…`) and in the Redis key. Bumping it invalidates all three cache layers at once; old entries age out on TTL. Keep `max-age=86400`.
- [x] Client-cancelled tile fetches no longer log as ERROR — handler returns 499 for `context.Canceled` (commit fc54703)
- [x] Restore terrain exaggeration for the Mapbox provider — the Settings slider re-applies terrain via `setTerrain` against an app-owned DEM source
- [ ] Sentry for error tracking (free tier)
- [ ] Mapbox token URL restrictions (lock pk.* token to production domain)
- [ ] Logger middleware drops optional http.ResponseWriter interfaces (Flush, Hijack, Push) — fix before adding SSE/WebSocket/streaming features
- [ ] Add integration test for duplicate-email 409 path (requires real Postgres)
- [ ] Capability-aware basemap cards (hide IGN/Sentinel when backend env vars not configured)
- [ ] BKG TopPlusOpen serves global tiles (tested: Madrid, Rome, London, Moscow, New York all return data) — consider expanding bbox or offering it as a global topo alternative
- [ ] Richer Swiss winter mode — add swisstopo winter overlays `ch.swisstopo.bahnen-winter` (cableways/skilifts) and `ch.swisstopo.unterkuenfte-winter` (winter huts) as `OVERLAY_SOURCES`, alongside the existing ski-touring / snowshoe
- [ ] Overlay catalog expansion (Phase 3 follow-on — the `OVERLAY_SOURCES` + Overlays-tab pattern already surfaces a toggle per source by filter):
  - Global hiking trails — add Waymarked Trails (`https://tile.waymarkedtrails.org/hiking/{z}/{x}/{y}.png`): global OSM-derived hiking routes, transparent raster, the hiking analog of the OpenSnowMap pistes overlay. No `topoSourceFilter`, available on any base/provider. Community service — consider proxying (User-Agent + caching) like OpenTopoMap. Waymarked Trails also offers cycling / MTB / winter-slope layers for later.
  - Swiss shooting ranges / live-fire zones — safety overlay; swisstopo/GeoAdmin WMTS (army firing-notice layer), `topoSourceFilter: 'swisstopo'`, same pattern as ski-touring/snowshoe. Switzerland-only — no meaningful global equivalent.
- [ ] When the swisstopo-winter layer swap (`pixelkarte-grau` → `pixelkarte-farbe-winter`) deploys, clear the stale tile cache: `redis-cli --scan --pattern 'tile:swisstopo-w:*' | xargs -r redis-cli del` — otherwise old grayscale tiles serve until the 24h TTL expires
- [x] Create custom Mapbox Studio winter style — done in Phase 3.5 M3 (Outdoors Winter, a custom style built on Mapbox Standard)
- [ ] Imported Studio styles (Outdoors / Outdoors Winter) — two benign console warnings, investigated and accepted; both fixable only in the style JSON, not app code:
  - Contour layer uses a `line-progress` expression but its source lacks `lineMetrics: true` → `line-progress … requires 'lineMetrics'` warning; contour lines don't draw with progress styling. (Contour tiles also 404 at low zoom — normal, contour data starts higher.) Fix: set `lineMetrics: true` on the contour source.
  - `Couldn't find terrain source "mapbox-dem"` — transient load-time noise. The style declares `terrain: {source: mapbox-dem}`, briefly processed before the app overrides terrain with its own `app-terrain-dem` source (which is what renders — `getTerrain()` confirms). Terrain works; `mapbox-dem` itself registers fine (its odd `tileSize: 514` is harmless). Do not re-investigate.
